Defendant James Travelle Jones in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:

The Court sentenced defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to any other sentence.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
-Restitution set at $4,540.00 payable to Walmart 
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments are to be collected during term of probation;  nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-No association with drug users, drug dealers and drug houses or otherwise engage in drug dealing
-Cooperate with agent
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-No contact with Walmart located at 4140 W. Greenfiled Avenue
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Perform 50 hours of community service
-Court allows for expungement if defendant successfully completes all terms and conditions of probation
-As a condition of probation, Court sentenced defendant to serve 30 DAYS in the House of Corrections, with Huber releases privileges for school and work.  Defendant to report to the House of Corrections on November 9, 2015 at 9:00a.m

Defendant James Travelle Jones in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Jeremy R. Arn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court involved in a Jury Trial.  Matter rescheduled for sentencing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 27, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant James Travelle Jones in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Defendant James Travelle Jones in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statement by State.  State recites defendant's juvenile record.  Defendant does not recall being adjudicated.  State to request juvenile record.  Matter adjourned for sentencing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 29, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY to the amended charge and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is  a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Amended Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Parties request adjournment for sentencing.
